 💡 Advantages

* Open-source and free
* CVE-based vulnerability detection
* Detailed and professional reports
* Risk prioritization using CVSS
* Scalable for enterprise environments



⚠ Limitations

* Cannot detect zero-day vulnerabilities
* Resource intensive (RAM/CPU)
* May generate false positives
* Requires proper configuration
* Active scans may affect system performance



🔐 Security Considerations

* Scanning should only be performed on:

  * Authorized systems
  * Controlled environments
* Unauthorized scanning is illegal



 🏁 Conclusion

> This project demonstrates how vulnerability assessment tools like GVM help organizations shift from reactive security to proactive risk management.

By identifying vulnerabilities early, organizations can:

